description: WWPKG Holdings Company Limited operates as a travel agent in Hong Kong and Macau. It designs, develops, and sells package tours; and sells air tickets and hotel accommodations, as well as ancillary travel related products and services under the WWPKG brand, as well as invests in tourism and travel technology related businesses. The company was founded in 1979 and is headquartered in Kowloon, Hong Kong. WWPKG Holdings Company Limited is a subsidiary of WWPKG Investment Holdings Limited.

Sing Lee Software (Group) Limited, an investment holding company, develops and sells information and network technologies and services to the financial industry in the People's Republic of China. It engages in the development and sale of software products; sale of related hardware products; and provision of technical support services. The company was founded in 1993 and is headquartered in Wan Chai, Hong Kong. Sing Lee Software (Group) Limited is a subsidiary of Goldcorp Industrial Limited.

Luxey International (Holdings) Ltd. is an investment company, which engages in the provision of online shopping services. The company employs 711 full-time employees The firm operates through two business segments. The Swimwear and Garment segment is engaged in the manufacturing and trading of swimwear and garment products. The On-line Shopping and Advertising segment is engaged in the provision of on-line shopping, advertising and media related services.

Satu Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, designs, develops, produces, and trades in homeware products. The company offers home decorations, bathroom accessories, and kitchenware and tableware under the Satu Brown brand name. It serves brand owners and licensee, chain supermarkets, and department stores through a third party e-commerce platform in the United Kingdom, United States, Denmark, France, Poland, Australia, Germany, Switzerland, Italy, and internationally. The company was founded in 2000 and is headquartered in Kwun Tong, Hong Kong.

KOS International Holdings Limited provides human resources (HR) services to clients from various industries in Hong Kong, Macau, and the People's Republic of China. It offers recruitment services, and secondment and payroll services. Its recruitment services include for various positions at all levels, including administrative, executive, managerial, and professional. The company also assists in payroll and other administration services at its clients' requests. KOS International Holdings Limited was founded in 2009 and is headquartered in Tsim Sha Tsui, Hong Kong. KOS International Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of KJE Limited.

Orient Securities International Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides brokerage, and underwriting and placing services in Hong Kong. It also offers margin financing and money lending, securities trading, nominee, and initial public offering financing services. The company was incorporated in 2009 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong.

Tree Holdings Limited is a holding company principally engaged in the sale of furniture and home accessories. The Company operating its business under the brand name of TREE. The Company’s products portfolio includes furniture and home accessories such as tables, chairs, storage products, sofas, beds, kitchenware, bed and bathroom related products, jars, cushions, mattresses, utensils and baskets, among others. The Company also engaged in the provision of styling and consulting services, consignment sales services, the distribution and licensing of its intellectual property rights, and operation of the cafe inside its retail shop.

Great World Company Holdings Ltd, an investment holding company, engages in property, forestry, and general trading, and advertising businesses in the People's Republic of China. It is involved in the property investment and development activities; and operation and management of residential and commercial properties. The company also cultivates forestry and wood material products, Chinese herbal medicine ingredients and specialty agricultural byproducts; sells processed and prepackaged food; and offers information consultation services. In addition, it engages in the provision of mobile advertising media services for property market customers; railroad magazine distribution; and e-commerce platform management. Additionally, the company distributes information technology products, industrial consumer products, as well as engages in related research and development, and product manufacturing activities. The company was formerly known as T S Telecom Technologies Limited and changed its name to Great World Company Holdings Ltd in November 2008. Great World Company Holdings Ltd was founded in 1991 and is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong.

Yuxing InfoTech Investment Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, primarily manufactures, sells, and distributes information home appliances and complementary products to consumer markets in the People's Republic of China, Hong Kong, the United States, Australia, and internationally. It operates through Information Home Appliances, Internet Data Centre (IDC), Investing, Leasing, and Other Operations segments. The company provides broadband internet digital audio and video products; and develops, constructs, operates, merges, acquires, and leases properties that are used as IDC. It also offers high digital set-top box (STB), hybrid dual mode STB, over-the-top /Internet protocol television STB, STB equipped with an Android system products, etc. In addition, the company trades in securities; invests in financial instruments; provides investment consultancy and trustee services; and holds and leases properties. Further, it is involved in the manufacture, sale, and trade of electronic components and miscellaneous products; provision of asset management services; research and development of software and hardware, and network technology services; and research and development, and software designing activities. The company was incorporated in 1999 and is headquartered in Beijing, the People's Republic of China.

Sino Splendid Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in publishing and events organizing business in Singapore and Hong Kong. It operates through four segments: Travel Media Business, Financial Magazine Business, Securities Investment, and Money Lending. The Travel Media Business segment provides advertising services through the Internet and travel magazines; organizes events; and publishes magazines. The Financial Magazine Business segment offers contents and advertising services in a financial magazine distributed in the People's Republic of China. The Securities Investment segment invests in securities. The Money Lending segment provides funds to clients and receives loan interest income in return. The company was formerly known as China.com Inc. and changed its name to Sino Splendid Holdings Limited in October 2013. Sino Splendid Holdings Limited was founded in 1974 and is headquartered in Sheung Wan, Hong Kong.

Global Strategic Group Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the copper trading business in the People's Republic of China. It operates through four segments: Trading of Copper, Trading of Petrochemicals, Natural Gas Operations, and Leasing Business. It also invests in natural gas projects; sells natural gas, natural gas cooking appliances, and accessories; and provides pipeline installation services. In addition, the company offers leasing services for steel support axial force servo system and technology support. Further, it offers internet and e-commerce solutions, IT consulting and technical services; commodity trading services; and designs and constructs energy power generation equipment, energy storage systems, and power equipment, as well as provides technology development, technical, and technology transfer services. The company was formerly known as DIGITALHONGKONG.COM and changed its name to Global Strategic Group Limited in January 2015. Global Strategic Group Limited is based in Wan Chai, Hong Kong.

Chinese Energy Holdings Ltd. operates as an investment company which engages in the provision of management services, investment in financial and investment products. The company employs 19 full-time employees The firm's subsidiaries include Growwise Holdings Limited, Top Connect Holdings Limited and First Top Finance Limited.

Jete Power Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, manufactures and sells cast metal products in Germany, Hong Kong, the People's Republic of China, the United States, and internationally. It operates through two segments, Metal Casting and Entertainment. The company provides pump, filter, valve, and food machinery components made from stainless steel, carbon steel, bronze, and/or grey iron. It serves suppliers of flow control devices, electromechanical equipment, and industrial machinery and equipment. The company also organizes concerts and events. Jete Power Holdings Limited was incorporated in 2014 and is headquartered in Sheung Wan, Hong Kong.

Polyard Petroleum International Group Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the exploration, exploitation, and development of oil and natural gas in the Philippines. The company holds interests in the Central Luzon gas project that covers approximately 6,840 square kilometers located in Central Luzon; and the South Cebu oil and gas project covering an area of 1,970 square kilometers located in Cebu Island. It also provides technical services; and consultancy services for oil and gas exploration and development, as well as trades in minerals, energy, and petroleum-related products. The company was formerly known as Kanstar Environmental Paper Products Holdings Limited and changed its name to Polyard Petroleum International Group Limited in November 2007. Polyard Petroleum International Group Limited is based in Wan Chai, Hong Kong. Polyard Petroleum International Group Limited is a subsidiary of Silver Star Enterprises Holdings Inc.

ECI Technology Holdings Limited is engaged in the provision of extra-low voltage (ELV) solutions. The Company's solutions include central control monitoring systems such as security system, car park system and clubhouse management system, and telecommunications and broadcasting services systems, such as CABD System and SMATV System. It sources hardware, such as security cameras, display devices, cables and wires, and electronic and electrical components, as well as systems such as smartcard and access control systems from local and overseas suppliers. It provides total security solutions, including access control, burglar alarm, time attendance, elevator control and door phone entry system. Its customers in the private sector are property developers and property management companies in Hong Kong. Its customers in the public sector are government departments, such as drainage services department, leisure and cultural services department, electrical and mechanical services department.

TradeGo FinTech Limited, an investment holding company, provides integrated securities trading platform services to brokerage firms and their clients in Hong Kong and the People's Republic of China. The company engages in the development of TradeGo Pro, a securities trading platform software. It offers front office trading system services to support trading of a range of financial instruments, including equities, ETFs, futures, options, warrants, and derivatives; value-added services; and other services, such as simulation trading platform, online account opening appointment, two-factor authentication, customized software development, cloud infrastructure and hosting, and online advertising services. In addition, the company holds market data vendor licenses from five stock and future exchanges, as well as provides a range of real-time market data feeds from these exchanges. Further, it develops computer hardware and software technology. The company was founded in 2011 and is headquartered in Hong Kong, Hong Kong.

Finsoft Financial Investment Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, primarily develops and sells financial trading software solutions. The company operates through Financial Trading Software Solutions, Other IT and Internet Financial Platforms Services, Money Lending, Assets Investments, and Others segments. The Financial Trading Software Solutions segment provides trading and settlement systems of financial products for financial institutions. The Other IT and Internet Financial Platforms Services offers e-commerce platforms, other online consultancy services, IT services, and other financial information. The Money Lending segment provides loan financing products. The Assets Investments segment trades in listed securities and invests in properties for rental income. The Others segment offers referral services to source, identify, and refer deal opportunities to interested parties; and corporate finance advisory services. This segment also trades in gaming products, as well as offers related marketing services. In addition, the company provides administrative support services; invests in securities and equity; and develops mobile e-commerce platform. It primarily serves financial institutions that conduct brokerage business of financial products traded in Hong Kong. The company was formerly known as Finsoft Corporation and changed its name to Finsoft Financial Investment Holdings Limited in June 2015. Finsoft Financial Investment Holdings Limited was incorporated in 2012 and is headquartered in North Point, Hong Kong.

Hao Wen Holdings Limited is an investment holding company principally engaged in the manufacture and trading of biomass fuel in the People’s Republic of China. The Company is also engaged in the money lending business and the sale of biodegradable food containers and disposable industrial packaging for consumer products in Hong Kong. The Company’s subsidiaries include Perfect Take Group Limited, Smart Courage Limited and Earth Buddy (Intellectual Property) Limited.

Grace Wine Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the production and distribution of wine products under the Grace Vineyard brand name in the People's Republic of China. It offers red, white, and sparkling types of wine. The company also engages in the plantation of vines; and sale of wine grapes. Grace Wine Holdings Limited was founded in 1997 and is based in Quarry Bay, Hong Kong.

Unitas Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides corporate finance advisory services primarily to listed and non-listed companies in Hong Kong, the People's Republic of China, and internationally. It operates through Corporate Finance Advisory Service; Dry Bulk Shipping and Logistic Services; and IP Automation and Entertainment Business segments. The company advises on the listing rules, growth enterprise market (GEM) listing rules, and takeovers codes; mergers and acquisitions activities; other corporate activities, such as fund raising exercises; and corporate resumptions, as well as acts as an independent financial adviser to transactions of listed issuers that are under the listing rules, GEM listing rules, and takeovers codes. It also provides automation gift machines, thematic game machines, and carnival game booths, as well as retails outlet. The company was formerly known as Chanceton Financial Group Limited and changed its name to Unitas Holdings Limited in October 2016. Unitas Holdings Limited was incorporated in 2011 and is headquartered in Tsim Sha Tsui, Hong Kong.

WLS Holdings Ltd. engages in the provision of construction services. The company employs 93 full-time employees The firm is also engaged in the provision of gondolas, parapet railings and access equipment installation and maintenance services. The Company’s subsidiaries include Bright Advantage Limited, Conkar Investments Limited and First Occasion Limited.

Evershine Group Holdings Ltd. engages in the investment business. The company employs 46 full-time employees Along with subsidiaries, the Company operates its business through five segments. The Property Development and Investment segment is mainly engaged in building construction, property development and construction materials trading and related consulting services and property leasing business in Turkey and Hong Kong. The Money Lending segment is engaged in money lending business in Hong Kong. The Trading segment is engaged in the trading of Onyx marbles and red wine. The Cemetery segment is engaged in the construction and operation of the cemeteries in Mainland China. The Mobile Application segment is engaged in development of mobile games, game publishing, applications, related intellectual property and platform, and provision of related solutions.

Kwong Man Kee Group Limited, an investment holding company, provides engineering services to the car park flooring industry in Hong Kong. The company offers flooring services, including application of proprietary floor coating products for providing a colorful, slip-resistance, and hard wearing surface that is resistant against water and petrochemicals; and ancillary services comprising specialized texture painting and waterproofing works. It also offers screeding and anti-skid surfacing services. The company was founded in 2002 and is headquartered in Kowloon, Hong Kong. Kwong Man Kee Group Limited is a subsidiary of Sage City Investments Limited.

Asian Capital Resources (Holdings) Limited is an investment holding company principally engaged in private securities investment, private equity investment, venture capital investment and the provision of business consultation services and private investment fund management services. The Company’s subsidiaries include Shanghai Zero2ipo M&A Fund Management Co., Ltd and Kasun Asian Capital Resources Management Limited.

China Brilliant Global Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the research and development, design, wholesale, and retail of gold and jewelry, and related ancillary businesses in Hong Kong and the Peoples' Republic of China. The company operates through Trading and Retailing of Gold and Jewellery, Lending Business, and Pharmaceutical and Healthcare Products segments. It is also involved in the distribution and retail of Chinese herbal medicines and drugs; internet artificial intelligence research, management, and consultancy activities; network and data services; and money lending business. The company was formerly known as Prosten Health Holdings Limited and changed its name to China Brilliant Global Limited in May 2018. China Brilliant Global Limited was incorporated in 1989 and is headquartered in Sheung Wan, Hong Kong. China Brilliant Global Limited is a subsidiary of Brilliant Chapter Limited.

KPM Holding Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the design, fabrication, installation, and maintenance of signage and related products in Singapore. Its signage and related products include indoor and outdoor, road, and hoarding signage, as well as steel works and railings. The company offers its products in public sector for roads, education institutions, public housing flats/compounds, defense compound, airport and national parks, and others; and private sector for commercial and industrial buildings, private residential buildings, hospitals, and fast food chains. KPM Holding Limited was founded in 1997 and is headquartered in Singapore.

Timeless Software Limited, an investment holding company, engages in mining business in the People's Republic of China. The company operates in two segments, Mining Business and Other Business. It explores, exploits, processes, and sells nickel and copper ores, as well as gold and iron ores. The company has interest in the Baishiquan nickel-copper mine located in Xinjiang. It is also involved in the provision of consultancy, software maintenance and development, and e-commerce services, as well as invests in IT and innovation projects, including e-Sport tournament organizing, bio and nano new materials, IT startup fund, and intelligent agricultural applications. In addition, the company engages in the technology and business investment activities; and research and development of Styrofoam. Timeless Software Limited was founded in 1996 and is based in Hong Kong, Hong Kong.

Sun International Group Limited, an investment holding company, provides equine and various financial services in Hong Kong and Australia. It operates through Financial Services and Equine Services segments. The Financial Services segment offers securities and futures brokerage, margin financing, and custodian services. The Equine Services segment engages in the trading and breeding of bloodstocks; and provision of stallion services. It also provides financial intermediary services for facilitating capital investment entrant scheme applications; and asset management services, which include investment management products comprises of managed accounts, hedge funds, private funds, dedicated funds, and investment advisory services. In addition, the company offers various financial products, such as personal and SME loans, home mortgages, corporate loans, equity financing, equity mortgage, and corporate finance; and human resources and administrative services, as well as invests in properties. The company was formerly known as Sun International Resources Limited and changed its name to Sun International Group Limited in December 2017. The company was incorporated in 2000 and is based in Kwun Tong, Hong Kong. Sun International Group Limited is a subsidiary of First Cheer Holdings Limited.

Flying Financial Service Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the provision of financial services to property developers and real estate development activities in the People's Republic of China. It operates through four segments: Investment in Property Development Projects; Operation of Financial Services Platform; Provision of Entrusted Loan, Pawn Loan, Other Loan Services, and Financial Consultation Services; and Finance Lease Services. The company offers short-term and long-term financial consultation services; and entrusted, pawn, and other loans to borrowers and financial institutions. It also provides long-term finance lease; investment income services; and operates a financial services platform. The company was founded in 2001 and is headquartered in Shenzhen, China. Flying Financial Service Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Ming Cheng Investments Limited.

ETS Group Ltd. is an investment holding company, which engages in the provision of multi-media contact services and contact center system. The company employs 688 full-time employees The firm operates through five business segments: outsourcing inbound contact service segment, outsourcing outbound contact service segment, staff insourcing service segment, contact service centre facilities management service segment and others segment. The Others segment is principally engaged in the licensing and sales of system and software, as well as the maintenance of system.

Viva China Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, operates as an integrated sports conglomerate in the People's Republic of China. It operates through two segments, Sports-Related Business and Sports Destinations Development. The Sports-Related Business segment produces and distributes sports content; manages and markets sports talents; and provides sports-related marketing and consultancy services. The Sports Destinations Development segment develops property for sales and investment; researches and develops, manufactures, markets, and sells construction materials; operates sports parks and centers, and ice-skating rinks; develops communities; and provides consultancy and subcontracting services. The company was formerly known as Coolpoint Energy Limited and changed its name to Viva China Holdings Limited in November 2010. The company was incorporated in 2000 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong.

Global Link Communications Holdings Ltd. is an investment holding company, which engages in the provision of solutions for train information systems and development of community mobile Internet applications. The company employs 207 full-time employees The firm operates through two business segments: the People’s Republic of China (the PRC) and Hong Kong. The firm is also involved in the holding of software rights, the development of community mobile Internet applications and provision of related services, as well as the provision of value-added telecommunications solutions, telecommunications application software and networking solutions through its subsidiaries.

Vodatel Networks Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, primarily engages in the design, sale, and implementation of network and systems infrastructure in Mainland China, Hong Kong, and Macau. It offers customer data automation, customization and integration, and technical support services; and IT and surveillance solutions for the public sectors, as well as the telecommunications, gaming, and hospitality sectors. The company engages in the research and development of software, and provision of related software consultancy services; and provision of wireless data communications and Internet related products and services. It offers computer software, hardware, and system integration services; cyber security, cloud security, and Internet of Things security solutions; cloud data center automation solutions; multi-cloud solutions for smart city; comprehensive enterprise solutions; and network management systems. The company sells data networking systems and provides related engineering services; and provides warehouse services. Vodatel Networks Holdings Limited is headquartered in Taipa, Macau.

Janco Holdings Limited is a Hongkong-based company principally engaged in the freight forwarding and the provision of logistics one-stop services. The Company mainly operates through two segments. The Freight Forwarding segment is mainly involved in the air freight and ocean freight. The Provision of Ancillary Logistics Service includes warehousing, repacking, labeling, palletizing and local delivery within Hongkong. The Company’s subsidiaries include Janco (BVI) Group Ltd, Marine Elite Limited, Sunset Edge Limited, as well as Wasco Global Limited, among others.

eBroker Group Limited, an investment holding company, provides financial software solution services to financial institutions in Hong Kong. The company's trading solution includes eBrokerSys, sponsored DMA, institutional sales desk solutions, and global futures and options trading platform; Algo solutions comprises Algo trader, volatility trading system, and market making system; investment solutions, such as alpha investment system, fund administration system, and wealth management system; and enterprise solutions consists of global back office system, portfolio risk reporting system, and data centers hosting and exchange colocation services. It also sells computer products. The company was founded in 2000 and is based in Central, Hong Kong.

China Biotech Services Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides medical laboratory testing and health check services. It operates through Immunotherapy, Pharmaceutical Products, Medical and Health Related Services, Securities, Insurance brokerage, and Others segments. The company also engages in the research, development, manufacture, sale, and distribution of health related and pharmaceutical products; trading of securities; money lending business; provision of tumor immune cell therapy, immune cell storage, and health management services; and provision of coordination of healthcare providers services. In addition, it markets and sells health supplements, Chinese medicines, slimming pills, and beauty products; trades in pharmaceutical intermediates; and offers insurance brokerage services. Further, the company provides molecular diagnostic test and genetic investigation, and property investment services. It has operations in the People's Republic of China and Hong Kong. China Biotech Services Holdings Limited has a strategic cooperation agreement with the Nanjing Medical University. The company was formerly known as Rui Kang Pharmaceutical Group Investments Limited and changed its name to China Biotech Services Holdings Limited in November 2017. China Biotech Services Holdings Limited was founded in 1996 and is headquartered in Causeway Bay, Hong Kong.

KNK Holdings Limited provides architectural and structural engineering consultancy services in Hong Kong. Its services include licensing consultancy; alteration and addition works and minor works consultancy; inspection and certification; and other architecture related consultancy. KNK Holdings Limited was founded in 1999 and is headquartered in Kwun Tong, Hong Kong.

DCB Holdings Limited is an investment holding company mainly engaged in the renovation work. Along with subsidiaries, the Company operates its business through two segments. The Renovation Work segment is involved in works carried out on existing buildings that involve upgrades and/or makeovers and/or demolition of existing works. The Fitting-Out Work segment is involved in works conducted on new buildings. It provides fitting-out and renovation services to different types of premises in the private sector, including residential apartments and residential dwellings, show flats, clubhouses, sale office, public area in residential and commercial buildings, office, shopping malls and shops. Its customers comprised property developers, some of which are (or whose holding companies are) listed on the Stock Exchange; main contractors or direct contractors of the fitting-out and renovation projects; and owners or tenants of properties.

Atlinks Group Limited, an investment holding company, designs, develops, and sells home and office telecommunication products to retailers, telecommunication operators, and distributors primarily in Europe and Latin America. The company develops and distributes telephones, monitoring solutions, baby monitors, and conferencing phones under the Alcatel brand; and landline phones, smart home accessories, mobile phones, and various services to support and reassure senior users under the Swissvoice brand. It also provides sound telephones, headphones, accessories, and mobile phones under the Amplicomms brand. In addition, the company develops and trades in electrical equipment, including radio communication equipment; and manages trademarks. The company was founded in 2013 and is based in Kowloon Bay, Hong Kong. Atlinks Group Limited is a subsidiary of Eiffel Global Limited.

Jiangsu NandaSoft Technology Company Limited, together with its subsidiaries, sells computer hardware and software products primarily in the People's Republic of China. It operates through three segments: Computer Hardware and Software Products; System Integration Service; and Property Investment. The company also engages in the trading of information technology related products and equipment; provision of information technology training services; and developing, manufacturing, and marketing of network security software, internet application software, education software, and business application software. In addition, it offers system integration services, as well as services related to building installation, and information system integration; invests in properties; and researches and develops medicine and pharmaceutical equipment. Further, it provides biological medicine, properties management services, communication intelligence control systems, and online education services. The company was formerly known as Jiangsu NandaSoft Company Limited and changed its name to Jiangsu NandaSoft Technology Company Limited in September 2008. Jiangsu NandaSoft Technology Company Limited was founded in 1998 and is based in Nanjing, China.

China Ocean Group Development Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the supply chain management, money lending, and ocean fishing businesses in the People's Republic of China, Hong Kong, and internationally. The company provides services involving the planning and implementation of an integrated solution for the flow of business, logistic, information, and funds to small and medium sized enterprises in various industries. It also offers money lending services. In addition, the company is involved in the fishing and catching business in an open sea. Further, it provides administration and ships building services; and trades in seafood products. The company was formerly known as China Ocean Fishing Holdings Limited and changed its name to China Ocean Group Development Limited in May 2020. China Ocean Group Development Limited was incorporated in 2001 and is headquartered in Wan Chai, Hong Kong.

Yu Tak International Holdings Ltd. is an investment company, which engages in the design and sale of gold and jewelry products. The company employs 130 full-time employees The firm operates through two business segments. The Jewelry Products segment is engaged in the design and sales of gold and jewelry products. The IT Products and Services segment is engaged in the provision of information technology services, including systems integration and professional services, as well as the sales of products, including enterprise software products.

long name: Jilin Province Huinan Changlong Bio-pharmacy Co Ltd
description: Jilin Province Huinan Changlong Bio-pharmacy Company Limited manufactures and distributes Chinese medicines and pharmaceutical products in the People's Republic of China. The company offers tablets, capsules, bulk drugs, pills, Chinese medicine pretreatment and extraction products, powders for injections, lyophilized powder for injections, small volume injection solutions, APIs, and granules and pills. It markets its products under the Changlong and Qing Tong brand names. The company was formerly known as Jilin Province Huinan Biochemical Pharmaceutical Company Limited. Jilin Province Huinan Changlong Bio-pharmacy Company Limited was founded in 1989 and is based in Tonghua, China.

description: Quantum Thinking Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the provision of system development and other value-added technical consultation services, and hardware-related businesses in the People's Republic of China. It operates through System Development, Consultancy, Maintenance and Other Services; and Sales of Hardware Products segments. The company engages in developing and establishing integrated online platforms for the distribution of mobile products, as well as online network systems; and technical and software development of identity authentication services related products. In addition, it provides IT network consultation services; and trades in residential gateway products. The company was formerly known as Yunbo Digital Synergy Group Limited and changed its name to Quantum Thinking Limited in December 2017. The company was incorporated in 2000 and is headquartered in Wan Chai, Hong Kong. Quantum Thinking Limited is a subsidiary of Happy On Holdings Limited.

CircuTech International Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the research and development, manufacture, marketing, and sale of video surveillance systems in North America, Europe, Asia, Africa, and internationally. It is also involved in the distribution of third party IT products; and provision of repair, maintenance, and other support services for electronic products. The company was formerly known as TeleEye Holdings Limited and changed its name to CircuTech International Holdings Limited in August 2016. CircuTech International Holdings Limited was founded in 1994 and is headquartered in Causeway Bay, Hong Kong. CircuTech International Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Foxconn (Far East) Limited.

long name: Luk Hing Entertainment Group Holdings Ltd
description: Luk Hing Entertainment Group Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the food and beverage, and entertainment businesses in Macau, Hong Kong, and the People's Republic of China. The company operates clubs and restaurants; and organizes music-related events, as well as grants loans to entities in the food and beverage, and entertainment industry. It is also involved in catering business. The company was incorporated in 2015 and is headquartered in Sheung Wan, Hong Kong. Luk Hing Entertainment Group Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Welmen Investment Co. Ltd.

description: Pizu Group Holdings Ltd. is an investment holding company, which engages in the civil explosive industry. The company employs 652 full-time employees The firm operates through two business segments. The Bulk Mineral Trade segment is engaged in the trading of non-ferrous metals and minerals in Hong Kong and the People’s Republic of China (the PRC) .The Explosives Trading and Blasting Services segment is engaged in the manufacturing and sales of explosives, operation of blasting and provision of related services in the PRC. The firm is also involved in the sourcing of production materials for group companies through its subsidiaries.

China E-Information Technology Group Limited, an investment holding company, provides internet platform for education programs in Chinese medicines, and other advisory and training programs in the People's Republic of China. The company offers occupational education, industry certification courses, skills training, and education consultation services; management services; distance learning program in Chinese medicine; and healthcare services. It also operates Chinese medicine health centers, and training centers. The company was formerly known as China E-Learning Group Limited and changed its name to China E-Information Technology Group Limited in June 2017. China E-Information Technology Group Limited was incorporated in 2001 and is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong.

Life Concepts Holdings Ltd. engages in the management of chain of restaurants. The company employs 634 full-time employees The firm principally engaged in the operation of a chain of restaurants in Hong Kong serving a variety of Asian, Western and Italian cuisines. The firm also provides catering management and design services.

Madison Holdings Group Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the retail and wholesale of various wine products and other alcoholic beverages in the People's of Republic of China, Hong Kong, Europe, and Japan. It operates through Sales of Alcoholic Beverages, Financial Services, Blockchain Services, Loan Financing Services, and Auction segments. Its agency brands include Vega Sicilia, Roy Estate, Lail Vineyards, Amuse Bouche, and Bass Phillip. The company also offers wine storage services; financial consultancy services; securities and futures dealing services; loan financing, micro financing, and loan referral services; and alcoholic beverages auction services. In addition, it provides transaction verification and computing services. The company was formerly known as Madison Wine Holdings Limited and changed its name to Madison Holdings Group Limited in July 2017. Madison Holdings Group Limited was founded in 1997 and is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong.

Glory Flame Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the provision of construction works and building materials supply activities in Hong Kong and the People's Republic of China. It offers concrete demolition and construction engineering services; undertakes construction works; and provides concrete coring, wall sawing and diamond wire cutting, and bridge and road saw cutting, as well as demolition through hydraulic crusher and burster, grouting and bar fixing, and various demolition robots. The company also trades in clean coal and others, and ecological LED cultivation cabinet systems. In addition, it is involved in the research and sale of LED cultivation cabinets; and manufacture and sale of prefabricated precast costruction components. Glory Flame Holdings Limited was incorporated in 2014 and is based in Tsim Sha Tsui, Hong Kong.

EFT Solutions Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides electronic fund transfer at point-of-sale (EFT-POS) solutions in Hong Kong, Australia, and internationally. It operates through Sale of Hardware Devices, and System Support and Software Solution Services segments. The company engages in sourcing EFT-POS terminals and peripheral devices, as well as providing EFT-POS system support services to various EFT-POS terminal manufacturers, acquirers, and merchants. description: Dadi International Group Ltd. is an investment company, which engages in the provision of medical information digitalization and media related services. The company employs 47 full-time employees Along with subsidiaries, the Company operates its business through two segments. The Advertising and Media Related Services segment is engaged in designing, production, acting as agency and placement of advertisements, information consulting and marketing planning in the People’s Republic of China (PRC). The Financial Leasing and Other Financial Services segment is engaged in the provision of financial leasing and other financial services in the PRC. In addition, the Company is also engaged in fund based environmental industry investment businesses.

abc Multiactive Limited, through its subsidiaries, designs and sells computer software in Hong Kong. It operates through two segments, Financial Solutions and Fintech Resources. The company offers OCTOSTP, a trading software package that is used for front and back-office trading in brokerages and securities divisions of banks. It also provides front office trading system, which include order management system, multi-markets handling services, and risk management system; back office trading system comprises order processing, master setting/e-FRR, corporate actions, and settlement services; and multi-asset class management, real-time risk management, and comprehensive order type services. In addition, the company offers Fintech resources services including, IT professional secondment services; and Fintech professional recruitment services. Further, it provides OCTOSTP that supports multi-markets and integrates with front and back office system. Additionally, the company offers professional and maintenance services; software rental and related services; and sells computer hardware products. It also provides FinCAD, a risk analytics and derivatives risk management software; Curtain, a document security system; and high frequency trading engine to support high frequency trade of brokerage houses. The company was incorporated in 2000 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong. abc Multiactive Limited is a subsidiary of Maximizer International Limited.

ZMFY Automobile Glass Services Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the sale of automobile glass with installation/repair services for private and public motor vehicles in the People's Republic of China. The company operates through four segments: Automobile Glass, Photovoltaic System, Business Consultancy Services, and Finance Leasing Services. It also trades in automobile glass to industry peers and the traders of automobile glass; and provides photovoltaic system installation, business consultancy, and finance leasing services. The company primarily serves insurance companies, and corporate and individual customers. It operates 29 service centers. ZMFY Automobile Glass Services Limited was founded in 1999 and is headquartered in Beijing, the People's Republic of China.

IMS Group Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, designs and sells light-emitting diode (LED) lighting products for retail stores of luxury brands in Hong Kong, the People's Republic of China, rest of Asia, Europe, and internationally. The company offers LED lighting fixtures; integrated LED lighting solution services, such as LED lighting system design; LED lighting system consultation and maintenance services; after-delivery maintenance and enhancement services; and on-site project management services, as well as project consultancy services. It also sells visual-audio systems, including audio/video conference, projection, public address, sound masking, and central controlling systems. IMS Group Holdings Limited was founded in 1998 and is headquartered in North Point, Hong Kong.

Honbridge Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the research, development, production, and sale of lithium battery in the People's Republic of China, Belgium, and Sweden. It operates through Mineral Resources Exploration and Trading; Lithium Battery Production; and Battery Swapping Service segments. The company also researches and explores mineral resources; trades in copper and steel; and provides power exchange services. In addition, the company researches and explores for iron ores in Brazil. The company is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong. Honbridge Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Hong Bridge Capital Limited.

long name: Zhejiang ChangAn Renheng Technology Co Ltd
description: Zhejiang Chang'an Renheng Technology Co., Ltd., together with its subsidiaries, develops, produces, and sells bentonite fine chemicals in the People's Republic of China. The company offers papermaking chemicals; inorganic gel; bentonite products for metallurgy pellets; quality calcium-bentonite products; organic bentonite products; and other chemicals, such as flocculating agents that are primarily used in the coating preparation industry. It is also involved in the mining and processing of clay; and wholesale and retail of chemicals and equipment. The company was formerly known as Changxing Renheng Fine Bentonite Co., Ltd. and changed its name to Zhejiang Chang'an Renheng Technology Co., Ltd. in December 2008. Zhejiang Chang'an Renheng Technology Co., Ltd. was founded in 2000 and is headquartered in Changxing, the People's Republic of China.

description: BOSA Technology Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides mechanical splicing services to the reinforced concrete construction industry in Hong Kong. It is involved in processing reinforcing bars, including cutting, crimping, chamfering, and threading of reinforcing bars at its premises or at the premises of customers; and connecting reinforcing bars by couplers. The company serves various contractors and subcontractors. BOSA Technology Holdings Limited was founded in 2012 and is headquartered in Kwun Tong, Hong Kong.

Tak Lee Machinery Holdings Ltd. is an investment company, which engages in the sale of heavy equipment and spare parts. The company employs 117 full-time employees The firm's product portfolio consists of various types of earthmoving equipment, including heavy vehicles and earthmoving attachments, as well as their spare parts. The firm's business segments are sales of heavy equipment and spare parts, leasing of heavy equipment, and maintenance and ancillary services. Its other products include other heavy equipment, such as high reach equipment, and power and energy equipment. The firm offers a range of heave equipment, such as excavators, bulldozers, soil compactor, wheel loader, vibratory roller, crawler drill and crawler loader. The firm is an authorized dealer of Hitachi brand heavy equipment in Hong Kong and Macau. The firm distributes heavy equipment of Labounty brand in Hong Kong and Macao, and Ramfos brand in Hong Kong, Macao and the People's Republic of China (PRC).

Good Fellow Healthcare Holdings Limited, formerly Hua Xia Healthcare Holdings Limited, is an investment holding company principally engaged in the operation of hospitals. The Company’s general hospital services mainly include the provision of medical wards, surgical wards, cosmetic surgery, dermatology and medical checkup and examination services, among others.

Millennium Pacific Group Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the research, development, manufacture, and sale of consumer electronic products in the People's Republic of China and Hong Kong. The company offers fitness bracelets, GPS personal navigation devices, mobile internet devices, and TV set-top boxes. It also trades in electronic devices; provides data management services; and develops and sells software applications. In addition, the company provides design, prototyping/sampling, manufacturing, assembling, and packaging services to customers' products. Millennium Pacific Group Holdings Limited was founded in 2004 and is headquartered in Shenzhen, the People's Republic of China.

Aurum Pacific (China) Group Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the development and marketing of server based technology, and provision of communications software platform and software related services in Hong Kong, Mainland China, and internationally. The company operates through Software Platform, Money Lending, and Mobile Gaming segments. Its information technology solutions facilitate government departments and corporations to communicate with their clients via websites, telephones, and mobile phones using interactive voice response system and mobile applications. The company also engages in the money lending business. In addition, it is involved in development and publishing of mobile games and applications, and related intellectual property and platform; development of mobile data solutions and related services; and provision of IT related solutions. In addition, it offers custom-made software development services. The company was formerly known as S & D International Development Group Limited and changed its name to Aurum Pacific (China) Group Limited in November 2008. Aurum Pacific (China) Group Limited is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong.

Altus Holdings Limited provides corporate finance and property investment services in Hong Kong and Japan. The company operates through Corporate Finance Services and Property Investment. It offers corporate finance services, including sponsorship, financial advisory, and compliance advisory services. The company also leases investment properties for residential and commercial use; and provides administrative services. Altus Holdings Limited was founded in 2000 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong. Altus Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Kinley-Hecico Holdings Limited.

Seamless Green China (Holdings) Limited, an investment holding company, manufactures and trades in LED and related products in the People's Republic of China, Hong Kong, and the Philippines. The company operates through LED, Optoelectronic, Liquor, and Sapphire segments. It supplies optoelectronic products and watch crystals for use in the watch products. The company also engages in the trading of wine and optoelectronic products; and property investment activities. Seamless Green China (Holdings) Limited was incorporated in 2001 and is headquartered in Sheung Wan, Hong Kong.

Bao Shen Holdings Limited engages in manufacturing and processing of plastic and steel components for white goods in the People's Republic of China. It offers stamping components and peripheral components that are used in white goods, including home washing machines and home refrigerators. The company is also involved in processing of spray-painting components and powder-coating components. It primarily sells its products to component processors and white goods manufacturers. The company was founded in 2010 and is headquartered in Chuzhou, the Peoples Republic of China. Bao Shen Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Wang Mao Investments Limited.

M&L Holdings Group Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the trading and leasing of construction machinery and spare parts in Hong Kong, the People's Republic of China, Singapore, and internationally. The company operates through two segments, Tunnelling and Foundation. It supplies specialized cutting tools and parts for tunnelling equipment manufacturers and microtunnelling equipment, as well as specialized construction equipment. The company also provides fabricated construction steel works and equipment; and repair and maintenance services. In addition, it is involved in the property investment business. M&L Holdings Group Limited was founded in 1994 and is headquartered in Tsimshatsui, Hong Kong. M&L Holdings Group Limited is a subsidiary of JAT United Company Limited.

Farnova Group Holdings Ltd, formerly Code Agriculture Holding Ltd, is an investment holding company principally engaged in the provision of digital television broadcasting and advertising. The Company operates its business through three segments. The Digital Television segment provides digital television broadcasting and advertising services. The Money Lending segment engages in the provision of mortgage loans and short term loans. The Securities Investments segment engages in the investments and trading of securities.

South China Assets Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the property development businesses in the People's Republic of China. It operates through two segments, Property Development and Financial Services. The company undertakes commercial and retail property development projects, such as shopping mall, entertainment, dining, and recreational facilities. It is also involved in money lending business; and the provision of investment advisory and asset management services, as well as deals in securities and futures, and insurance and mandatory provident fund service. The company was formerly known as South China Land Limited and changed its name to South China Assets Holdings Limited in January 2016. South China Assets Holdings Limited is based in Central, Hong Kong.

Sinopharm Tech Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in lottery business in the People's Republic of China and Hong Kong. It operates through Provision of Lottery-Related Services, Provision of Internet Plus Services, Manufacturing and Distribution of Personal Protective Equipment, and Other Services segments. The company offers lottery-related hardware and software systems. It also provides Internet plus solution services to government affair, public security, health care, leasing, and lottery industries; and corporate management services. The company was formerly known as China Vanguard You Champion Holdings Limited and changed its name to Sinopharm Tech Holdings Limited in June 2019. Sinopharm Tech Holdings Limited was founded in 1999 and is headquartered in Sha Tin, Hong Kong.

China Regenerative Medicine International Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the research and development of bio-medical and healthcare products, and medical techniques. It operates through Dermatology, Cosmetic products, and others; Cell and Healthcare products and services; Ophthalmology products; Stomatology products and others; and Medical Equipment segments. The company offers ActivSkin, a tissue-engineered skin product; Acornea, an acellular corneal stroma; Gegreen, a protein-detracted bone substitute material for inducing natural bone regeneration; Asiunin, an acellular anal fistula repair stroma; Megreen, an oral cavity repair membrane; and CS-ACI, a cell sheet-autologous chondrocyte implantation. It also manufactures and sells skincare products under the AMYbio and Ascara brands. In addition, the company provides human cell separation, purification, cultivation, amplification, and storage and transportation; develops and produces automated closed cell bioreactors; and sells and distributes medical products and equipment. Further, it offers contract research services, including drug screening, drug efficacy, and toxicity assays to institutions and hospitals. The company was formerly known as China Bio-Med Regeneration Technology Limited and changed its name to China Regenerative Medicine International Limited in March 2015. China Regenerative Medicine International Limited was founded in 1995 and is headquartered in Tsim Sha Tsui, Hong Kong.

Glory Mark Hi-Tech (Holdings) Limited, an investment holding company, designs, manufactures, and sells computer connectivity products. It operates through Original Equipment Manufacturer (OEM) Customers, Retail Distributors, and Provision of Comprehensive Architectural Services segments. The company offers computer peripheral products, multi-media consumable electronic products, communication products, automobile electronics accessories, wire harness, medical equipment, and VGA cables. The company also offers electronic products, such as USB hubs and card readers, cable series, lightning products, docking stations, wireless charging, HDMI, display port, dongles, and adapters. Further, the company is involved in master planning, general design, and architectural schematic design works. It sells its connectivity products to OEM customers and retail distributors in the People's Republic of China, Taiwan, Korea, Japan, the United States, and internationally. Glory Mark Hi-Tech (Holdings) Limited was founded in 1990 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong.

Goldway Education Group Limited, an investment holding company, provides tutoring services under the Logic Tutorial Centre name to primary and secondary school students in Hong Kong. It operates through two segments, Primary Tutoring Services and Secondary Tutoring Services. The Primary Tutoring Services segment provides tutoring services to primary school students from primary 1 to 6 who seeks to enhance their performance in formal school and in examination settings; and assists these younger students in solidifying the foundational knowledge necessary for them to succeed through the school system. The Secondary Tutoring Services segment offers tutoring services to secondary school students from secondary 1 to 6 who seeks to enhance their school performance for specific subjects; and prepare for public examinations. As of March 31, 2020, it operated 11 centers. Goldway Education Group Limited was founded in 2003 and is headquartered in Tuen Mun, Hong Kong.

MediNet Group Limited is principally engaged in the provision of corporate medical and dental solutions to customers, and the provision of different combinations of medical and/or dental services, as well as the operation of MediNet Centres and Dental Clinics. The Company operates in two segments. Dental Solutions and Dental Services segment involves in the provision of dental solutions and dental services by dental clinics owned and operated by the Company. Medical Solutions and Medical Services segment involves in the provision of medical solutions and operation of medical centres offering outpatient general services and men’s health treatments. Its subsidiaries include Medinet (BVI) Limited, MediNet Health Centre Limited, MediNet Services Limited and Well Being Dental Services Limited, among others.

Loco Hong Kong Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the trade of metal and commodity forward contracts in Hong Kong and the People's Republic of China. The company primarily trades in silver, gold, and tin metals, as well as processes silver products. It also engages in the provision of money lending and education management services. The company serves licensed banks and metal traders in Hong Kong, Singapore, Japan, Taiwan, Australia, the United Kingdom, and Dubai. Loco Hong Kong Holdings Limited was founded in 2009 and is headquartered in Admiralty, Hong Kong.

Merdeka Financial Group Limited, an investment holding company, engages in trading, financial services, and information technology businesses in Hong Kong and the People Republic of China. Its Trading Business segment trades in goods, components, and accessories; and retails milk powder, dairy products, beauty and cosmetic products, and pharmaceutical OTC products. The company's Financial Services Business segment provides financial leasing, money lending, corporate finance advisory, asset management, and securities brokerage services. Its Information Technology Business segment engages in the distribution of information technology products, and provision of relevant technical support services; developing mobile and cloud based application software; and operating e-commence and e-marketing businesses. The company's Corporate Consulting Business segment provides company secretarial, accounting, and financial reporting services; and management consulting services. The company was formerly known as Merdeka Financial Services Group Limited and changed its name to Merdeka Financial Group Limited in October 2019. Merdeka Financial Group Limited is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong.

China Eco-Farming Limited, an investment holding company, provides one-stop value chain services in Hong Kong, the People's Republic of China, and Taiwan. The company is involved in the provision of value chain services, including trading, packaging, and logistics solutions; and trade of consumables and agricultural products, as well as grocery food products. It also engages in the rental of investment properties; and provision of financial and investment advisory, corporate finance, securities holding, and money lending services, as well as trades in recycle bags. The company was formerly known as Linefan Technology Holdings Limited and changed its name to China Eco-Farming Limited in October 2009. China Eco-Farming Limited was incorporated in 2000 and is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong.

Neo Telemedia Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the sale of telecommunication products and services in Hong Kong, the People's Republic of China, and other Asian country. The company operates through Sale of Telecommunication Products and Services; and Internet Finance Platform segments. It also operates commercial WIFI and Internet finance platforms; provides value-added telecommunication and Internet data center services; and designs, manufactures, and sells logistics equipment. In addition, the company trades in mobile phones; and offers insurance brokerage services. The company was formerly known as Big Media Group Limited and changed its name to Neo Telemedia Limited in November 2009. Neo Telemedia Limited is headquartered in Wan Chai, Hong Kong.

Amasse Capital Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides corporate finance advisory services in Hong Kong. The company offers financial advisory services to listed companies and investors seeking to control or invest in public listed companies, as well as independent board committees and/or independent shareholders of public listed companies. It also acts as an underwriter and/or placing agent not holding client assets in fund raising activities for its clients. The company was incorporated in 2017 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong. Amasse Capital Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Access Cheer Limited.

Eco-Tek Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the research, development, marketing, sale, and servicing of industrial environmental protection related products and services in Hong Kong, the People's Republic of China, and internationally. The company operates through two segments, Environment-Friendly Products and Water Supply Plant. It markets and sells environment-friendly products, and operates water supply plant, as well has holds intellectual properties. The company was founded in 1999 and is headquartered in Quarry Bay, Hong Kong. Eco-Tek Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Team Drive Limited.

Lajin Entertainment Network Group Ltd. is an investment holding company, which engages in artist management and film production. The company employs 51 full-time employees The firm operates through two business segments. The Artists Management segment is mainly engaged in the provision of artists management services. The Movies, Television (TV) programs and Internet Contents segment is engaged in the investment, production and distribution of movies, TV programs and investment in Internet contents. The firm mainly conducts its businesses in Hong Kong and the People’s Republic of China (the PRC). The firm is also engaged in the cultural and entertainment related businesses through its subsidiaries.

Union Asia Enterprise Holdings Ltd. engages in the trading business. The company employs 15 full-time employees Together with subsidiaries, the Company operates business through two segments. Metals segment is engaged in the trading of stainless steel. The Company’s stainless steel wires are applied in the manufacturing of electric appliances, mobile communication equipment and highly precise surgical instruments. Securities segment engages in the investment and trading of listed securities.

China Digital Culture (Group) Limited, an investment holding company, engages in licensing and sale of entertainment, and sports and music content in the People's Republic of China. It operates through Entertainment, Sports, and Theme Park segments. The Entertainment segment engages in the business of training, nurturing, and managing eSports teams and eSports broadcasters; distribution of copyright-protected items; production of television drama series and talent management; provision of consultancy services in the cultural industry; and provision of entertainment-related services. The Sports segment is involved in the licensing of professional sports events content; and provision of marketing and promotional services to professional athletes. The Theme park segment operates film-based cultural parks and tourism projects. The company also engages in entertainment project planning and celebrity management activities; production of online streaming content. In addition, it engages in the celebrity and artists training course agency business; selling learning materials; and provision of consulting, and sponsorship and student tuition services. The company was formerly known as China Digital Licensing (Group) Limited. China Digital Culture (Group) Limited was incorporated in 2002 and is headquartered in Hong Kong, Hong Kong.

SuperRobotics Ltd. is an investment company, which engages in the sale of beauty products and provision of therapy services. The company employs 191,000 full-time employees The firm is also engaged in the beauty businesses, including the development, distribution and marketing of personal care treatments, products and provision of therapy services. The firm mainly conducts its businesses in Hong Kong and the People’s Republic of China (the PRC). The firm is also involved in the provision of related customer support services through its subsidiaries. The Company’s principal subsidiaries include Century Capital, Century Finance (BVI) Limited and China Honest Enterprises Limited.

China Information Technology Development Limited, an investment holding company, operates as an information technology (IT) company in the People's Republic of China. It operates through four segments: Software Development and System Integration, IT Infrastructure Solutions and Maintenance, Money Lending, and Securities Investments. The company develops and sells computer software and hardware; and provides system integration and related support, IT infrastructure solutions and maintenance, money lending, and securities trading services. It also offers office management services; big data application services; and asset acquisition, management, and consultancy services. The company was formerly known as Xteam Software International Limited. China Information Technology Development Limited was founded in 2001 and is headquartered in Kwun Tong, Hong Kong.

Food Idea Holdings Ltd. is an investment holding company, engages in the management of Chinese restaurants. The company employs 260 full-time employees The firm operates through four business segments. The Catering Services segment is engaged in the operation of chain restaurants. The Food Products Operation segment is engaged in the production, sales and distribution of food products, such as barbequed food and Taiwanese Lou Mei. The Investments segment is engaged in the investment in securities. The Money Lending segment is engaged in the provision of money lending business. The firm is also involved in the property holding, exclusive rights holding and central procurement operation businesses through its subsidiaries.

Shi Shi Services Limited, an investment holding company, provides property management services in Hong Kong and the People's Republic of China. The company operates in three segments: Provision of Property Management and Related Services, Properties Investment, and Money Lending Business. It offers security, repair and maintenance, cleaning, finance management, and administrative and legal support services to residential and commercial properties under the Kong Shum brand name. The company was formerly known as Heng Sheng Holdings Limited and changed its name to Shi Shi Services Limited in October 2018. The company was founded in 1984 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong. Shi Shi Services Limited is a subsidiary of Heng Sheng Capital Limited.

IR Resources Limited, an investment holding company, primarily engages in forestry and agricultural, financial services, cultural, and logistics businesses in the People's Republic of China and Hong Kong. It is involved in timber logging, as well as the plantation and sale of wood and agricultural products. The company also plants and cultivates rubber trees for latex production; and distributes agricultural products. In addition, it provides securities brokerage and trading services; underwriting and placing services; asset management services; and loan financing services. Further, the company develops and upgrades Chinese cultural related online application. It owns three forests measuring 31,000 hectares in Kratie Province, the Kingdom of Cambodia. The company was formerly known as China Asean Resources Limited and changed its name to IR Resources Limited in August 2015. IR Resources Limited is headquartered in Tsim Sha Tsui, Hong Kong.

Jimu Group Limited, an investment holding company, designs, develops, sources, markets, and sells footwear to wholesalers and retailers in Hong Kong, the People's Republic of China, Australia, the United Kingdom, New Zealand, Belgium, the United Arab Emirates, the United States, Chile, and internationally. It operates through Footwear Business and Loan Facilitation Service segments. The company offers formal and casual footwear for men, women, and children, as well as provides logistics management services. In addition, it provides loan facilitation services, which assist the qualified borrowers to obtain financing from various financial institutions or investors who have registered with online information intermediary service platforms. The company's pre-loan and post-loan facilitation services comprise business consulting and credit assessment services. As of December 31, 2019, it offered its loan facilitation services to individual customers through approximately 50 branch offices in the People's Republic of China. The company was formerly known as Ever Smart International Holdings Limited and changed its name to Jimu Group Limited in February 2018. The company was founded in 2009 and is headquartered in Kowloon, Hong Kong. Jimu Group Limited is a subsidiary of Jimu Group Holdings Limited.

GME Group Holdings Limited provides civil engineering services in Hong Kong. The company provides underground construction services, which includes tunnel construction, such as excavation, shotcreting, shutter design and fabrication, tunnel lining services, and advanced and structural works; and utility construction and other services, including construction and refurbishment of gas pipelines and electricity cables. It primarily serves main contractors in public sector infrastructure projects. GME Group Holdings Limited was founded in 1994 and is headquartered in Hong Kong, Hong Kong.

Loto Interactive Ltd, formerly MelcoLot Ltd, is an investment holding company mainly engaged in the provision of data analysis and storage services. Together with its subsidiaries, the Company operates business through its three operating segments. The Big Data Center Services segment engages in operation of two big data centers, which provide services including premises, hardware support, power supply, ancillary supervision and management services. The Online Game Business segment engages in the distribution of online mobile games. The Lottery Business segment engages in the trading of lottery terminals and parts and provision of services and solutions for the distribution of lottery products.

long name: Tianjin TEDA Biomedical Engineering Co Ltd
description: Tianjin TEDA Biomedical Engineering Company Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the research, development, manufacture, and sale of biological compound fertilizer products in the People's Republic of China. The company operates in two segments, Biological Compound Fertilisers Products, and Elderly Care and Health Care Services. Its biological compound fertilizer products are used for the facilitation of balanced growth of grains, fruits, and vegetables. The company is also involved in the provision of integrated elderly and health care, as well as consulting, advisory, and assessment services. In addition, it provides and licenses electroencephalography photography (EEG) diagnosis detection services; and conducts EEG detection and diagnosis technology services. Further, the company engages in the research, development, manufacturing, and application of biomedical science and technology projects; regional soil resources conditioning and remediation; and soil environmental quality standards research services. The company has a strategic cooperation agreement with Almage Group. Tianjin TEDA Biomedical Engineering Company Limited was founded in 2000 and is headquartered in Tianjin, the People's Republic of China.

description: Hong Wei (Asia) Holdings Company Limited, an investment holding company, manufactures and sells particleboards in the People's Republic of China and other Asian countries. It operates through two segments, Particleboards and Forestry. The company's products are primarily used in the production of furniture and fixtures; sports equipment; and decoration and construction materials. It is also involved in the plantation, timber logging, and sale of wood and agricultural products. The company markets and sells its products to home or office furniture manufacturers, sport equipment manufacturers, and wood-based panel processors and traders. Hong Wei (Asia) Holdings Company Limited was founded in 1993 and is headquartered in San Po Kong, Hong Kong.

description: Asia-Pac Financial Investment Co. Ltd. is an investment holding company, which engages in the provision of integrated professional services to public and private companies and individual investors. The company employs 54 full-time employees The firm operates through four business segments. The Asset Advisory Services and Asset Appraisal segment is engaged in the provision of asset appraisal and asset advisory services, including real estate and fixed asset appraisal, mineral property appraisal, business and intangible asset valuation, financial instrument and derivative valuation. The Corporate Services and Consultancy segment is engaged in the provision of company secretarial services, human resource management and other administrative services, corporate communication, marketing and governance services. The Media Advertising segment is engaged in the provision of media advertising related services.
